The thing about troubled banks is:
=09There is no better news story, for a troubled bank, than =E2=80=9CTroubl=
ed Bank Raises Equity Capital.=E2=80=9D The trouble, at a troubled bank, al=
ways is that the market has lost faith that its assets have enough value to=
 pay back all of its creditors (depositors, etc.) with an ample cushion of =
shareholder money left over. Raising money from shareholders just=C2=A0fixe=
s the trouble. Oh there=E2=80=99s other stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0probably earni=
ngs are going to be rough for a while even after the balance-sheet hole is =
filled, and you=E2=80=99ve got to fix whatever management problems led to t=
he trouble =E2=80=94=C2=A0but at some level a troubled bank is just a binar=
y question=C2=A0=E2=80=94 will it fix its balance-sheet hole or not? =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and if it does, then the stock should rally.=09There is no worse n=
ews story, for a troubled bank, than =E2=80=9CTroubled Bank Tries to Raise =
Equity Capital.=E2=80=9D The market practice, these days, is that troubled =
banks try to raise capital=C2=A0quietly, and then go out and announced that=
 they have=C2=A0done it. If they announce that they=E2=80=99re=C2=A0trying,=
 that suggests to the market that their discreet calls to potential investo=
rs didn=E2=80=99t work, and it causes panic. There are many reasons that   =
Silicon Valley Bank failed last year, but a big one is that, when it ran in=
to trouble, it=C2=A0launched a public stock offering=C2=A0to fix the troubl=
e. The offering itself caused a panic that sank the bank.
  [8]



These two facts suggest an investment opportunity: If you=C2=A0see a news s=
tory like=C2=A0=E2=80=9CTroubled Bank Tries to Raise Equity Capital,=E2=80=
=9D you call it immediately and offer to put in enough money to fill its ca=
pital hole, fix the problem, and cause a huge rally in the stock. And you o=
ffer to do it at an absolute bargain-basement price, because otherwise that=
 stock is going to zero.
I suppose they suggest another investment opportunity: If a troubled bank c=
alls you quietly looking to raise equity capital, and maybe somehow, throug=
h no fault of your own of course, it=C2=A0leaks out=C2=A0that the bank is l=
ooking to raise money, you=E2=80=99ll probably get a good price on the shar=
es.
