important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a> But it=E2=80=99s a clever=C2=A0<em>trade=C2=A0</em>by whoever this hol=
der was: The old=C2=A0bonds are far out-of-the-money (that is, they=E2=80=
=99re not going to convert into stock), and Bloomberg tells me that they we=
re trading in the high 70s as recently as a month ago (the high 80s more re=
cently). If you had noticed Avid=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>extremely technical oop=
sie</em>, you could have bought the bonds at, say, 80 cents on the dollar, =
sent them a letter saying =E2=80=9Cwe gotcha hahahaha,=E2=80=9D and made a =
