<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The thing about troubled banks is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is no better news story, for a =
troubled bank, than =E2=80=9CTroubled Bank Raises Equity Capital.=E2=80=9D =
The trouble, at a troubled bank, always is that the market has lost faith t=
hat its assets have enough value to pay back all of its creditors (deposito=
rs, etc.) with an ample cushion of shareholder money left over. Raising mon=
ey from shareholders just=C2=A0<em>fixes the trouble</em>. Oh there=E2=80=
=99s other stuff =E2=80=94=C2=A0probably earnings are going to be rough for=
 a while even after the balance-sheet hole is filled, and you=E2=80=99ve go=
t to fix whatever management problems led to the trouble =E2=80=94=C2=A0but=
 at some level a troubled bank is just a binary question=C2=A0=E2=80=94 wil=
l it fix its balance-sheet hole or not? =E2=80=94=C2=A0and if it does, then=
 the stock should rally.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is =
no worse news story, for a troubled bank, than =E2=80=9CTroubled Bank Tries=
 to Raise Equity Capital.=E2=80=9D The market practice, these days, is that=
 troubled banks try to raise capital=C2=A0<em>quietly</em>, and then go out=
 and announced that they have=C2=A0<em>done it</em>. If they announce that =
they=E2=80=99re=C2=A0<em>trying</em>, that suggests to the market that thei=
r discreet calls to potential investors didn=E2=80=99t work, and it causes =
panic. There are many reasons that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/34603555.257368/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDMtMTAvc3RhcnR1cC1iYW5rLWhhZC1hLXN0YXJ0dXAtYmFuay1yd=
W4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDMwNzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNl=
PW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzA3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB2e0e5302" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Silicon Valley Bank failed</a> last =
year, but a big one is that, when it ran into trouble, it=C2=A0<em>launched=
 a public stock offering=C2=A0</em>to fix the trouble. The offering itself =
caused a panic that sank the bank.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#foot=
