<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If=C2=A0<em>I were=C2=A0</em>doing a merger ho=
ax, I would put out the fake press release at like 10:29 a.m. and then=C2=
=A0<em>sit at my computer for five minutes</em>, with my brokerage account =
website open, ready to hit the =E2=80=9Csell=E2=80=9D button as soon as the=
 price went up. (Not legal, or illegal, advice.) But for some reason nobody=
 ever executes this trade correctly.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The inverse trade is: You=C2=A0<em>short=C2=A0=
</em>stock in a company (or buy puts, etc.), you make a=C2=A0<em>fake bankr=
uptcy filing </em>on behalf of the company, automated news-writing algorith=
